title: His Protecter
body:
read it on the AO3 at https://ift.tt/2THrVoq

by ObsidianDestiny

For years Tony Stark has kept his daughter safe despite the stereotypical kidnapping plots as Tony Starks daughter and Heiress.

He helped her design her suit and mask when she developed her powers and Joined the X-Men keeping her identity as a mutant a secret. The only ones he trusted were The Rogue Avengers who now broke his trust.

Now it’s her turn to protect her Father, she will do what it takes to keep him safe from fake friends and Allies. When the Rogues return they will have a rude awakening.

summary: dying in peters arms
body:
dying in peters arms

  • it’s a sad one lol, it’s also so bad??
  • i don’t know why i decided to do this as a head canon but let’s roll with it
  • let’s just say you got hit whilst fighting some sort of bad guy, and peter didn’t notice you were slowly dying because you didn’t seem effected by it
  • but like not even a minute later you dropped to the floor, and he was by your side in an instant.
  • there was so much blood, and it was coming from your chest. peter was a smart boy, so he knew then and there that he was gonna lose you.
  • so he just held you in his arms, whispering to you how it was all gonna be okay
  • and you’d stutter out that he needed to take care of himself, and he promised that he would
  • he placed gentle kisses to your forhead as you took your final breaths
  • and then he lets the tears roll

Peter Parker has been Spider-Man for a few years now and he’s learning fast how much life costs. Between the price of the tech he needs for his suit upgrades and the amount he’s going to need to go to college, he knows Aunt May won’t be able to pay for everything and neither will his job at the Daily Bugle.

He decides to start looking at some options. Other than loans or scholarships he sees a website for Sugar Daddies, who are more Ethan happy to pay for a bit of company.
